The Health Minister, Dr Zweli Mkhize announced that the total number of confirmed Covid-19 cases in South Africa is 10 015 as at Sunday, 10 May. This is an increase of 595 confirmed cases from the previous days report. Dr Mkhize said that it is noted with concern that the Eastern Cape and Western Cape combined comprises 84% of the total new cases. Provincial Breakdown: Province        Confirmed Cases           Deaths    Recoveries      Eastern Cape           1218                           22           519         Free State                 135                             6           105             Gauteng                  1952                           22          1247                KwaZulu â€“ Natal      1353                            43           606         Limpopo                     54                              3             28              Mpumalanga               61                              0             22              North West                 45                              0             23              Northern Cape            29                              0             16              Western Cape         5168                             98          1607                                          10 015                            194          4173 Testing data A total of 341 336 tests have been conducted to date of which 17 257 are new tests from those reported previously. This is a record high of 24 hour cycle of testing.  Sector             Total tested                New tested  Private             168 539      49%                7 642       44% Public               172 797      51%                9 615       56% Grand Total     341 336                        17 257 New deaths: 8 (1 E/Cape, 3 W/Cape, 4 Gauteng)  Total deaths = 194 Total Recoveries: 4173